<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="B" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Back2" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Back,</orth> adv., 1) turning or returning from a place or person: <bibl n="shak. ven 557" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 557</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ven 557" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 557</bibl> Lucr. Arg. <bibl n="shak. ven 557" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 557</bibl> <bibl n="shak. luc 843" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 843</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. luc 843" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 843</bibl> <bibl n="shak. luc 843" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 843</bibl> <bibl n="shak. luc 843" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 843</bibl> <bibl n="shak. son 126.6" default="NO" valid="yes">Sonn. 126, 6</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tmp 2.1.259" default="NO" valid="yes">Tp. II, 1, 259</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tmp 5.36.259" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 36</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tgv 4.4.57" default="NO" valid="yes">Gentl. IV, 4, 57</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wiv 5.5.89" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. V, 5, 89</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mm 1.1.75" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. I, 1, 75</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mm 2.2.143" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 2, 143</bibl> (<emph>turn b.</emph>) <bibl n="shak. err 4.2.55" default="NO" valid="yes">Err. IV, 2, 55</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mnd 3.2.315" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. III, 2, 315</bibl> etc. etc. <cit><quote>back again:</quote> <bibl n="shak. son 45.11" default="NO" valid="yes">Sonn. 45, 11</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. tmp 1.2.150" default="NO" valid="yes">Tp. I, 2, 150</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tgv 1.2.51" default="NO" valid="yes">Gentl. I, 2, 51</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mm 2.2.58" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. II, 2, 58</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. err 2.1.75" default="NO" valid="yes">Err. II, 1, 75</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mnd 1.1.251" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. I, 1, 251</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mv 1.1.151" default="NO" valid="yes">Merch. I, 1, 151</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mv 2.7.14" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 7, 14</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lr 4.2.91" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. IV, 2, 91</bibl> etc. <cit><quote>urge her to a present answer b.</quote> <bibl n="shak. aww 2.2.67" default="NO" valid="yes">All's II, 2, 67</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>goes to and b.</quote> <bibl n="shak. ant 1.4.46" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. I, 4, 46</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>b. my ring!</quote> <bibl n="shak. cym 2.4.118" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. II, 4, 118</bibl></cit>. <emph>give b.</emph> == yield, <bibl n="shak. tgv 5.4.126" default="NO" valid="yes">Gentl. V, 4, 126</bibl> (cf. <emph>give</emph>). <emph>to go b.</emph> == to give way, to succumb, get the worst: <cit><quote>goest thou b.? thou shalt go b., I warrant thee,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ant 5.2.155" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. V, 2, 155</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>make her go b., even to the yielding,</quote> <bibl n="shak. cym 1.4.115" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. I, 4, 115</bibl></cit>.<lb />2) not coming forward: cf. <emph>to keep, to stand</emph> etc.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>